    "body": "### Problem\n\nDoes anyone know if vim.lsp.rpc.connect() should work with a hostname or is it IP only.\r\n\r\nIt works perfectly with 127.0.0.1 but localhost returns the below. In the docs the field is called host, so I don't see anything that suggests it should be IP only. \r\n\r\nAnybody more familiar with the LUV TCP stuff?\r\n\r\nPerhaps there should be a resolution step in rpc.lua to be able to function with hostnames too?\r\n\r\n```/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/rpc.lua:706: Invalid IP address or port [localhost:5000]```\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nNo\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo connect via hostname \n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11 dev\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nAny LSP over tcp\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 22.04\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
